{
  "texts": [
    "For this study, we arbitrarily chose a window of 40ms, with the peak being the exact center.",
    "For all four time windows, we found occipital electrodes to be the most important, as was already suspected from the contour plots.",
    "All three stimulus types show a high agreement.",
    "The top three electrodes are always centered and further elec- trodes in the 90th percentile centered and on the right side, with only very few electrodes on the left side (Fig. 6).",
    "Furthermore, calculating the ERPs on basis of the most important electrodes identified by SHERPA, reveals the typical waveform (Fig. 7)."
  ]
}